{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":996,"text":"Tonight, I'm going to try to make the case"},{"time":3073,"text":"that inviting a loved one, a friend\nor even a stranger"},{"time":7699,"text":"to record a meaningful interview with you"},{"time":10130,"text":"just might turn out to be one of the most \nimportant moments in that person's life,"},{"time":14536,"text":"and in yours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17481,"text":"When I was 22 years old,\nI was lucky enough to find my calling"},{"time":20825,"text":"when I fell into making radio stories."},{"time":23285,"text":"At almost the exact same time,"},{"time":25719,"text":"I found out that my dad,\nwho I was very, very close to, was gay."},{"time":30688,"text":"I was taken completely by surprise."},{"time":32990,"text":"We were a very tight-knit family,"},{"time":35498,"text":"and I was crushed."},{"time":37889,"text":"At some point, in one\nof our strained conversations,"},{"time":40234,"text":"my dad mentioned the Stonewall riots."},{"time":42904,"text":"He told me that one night in 1969,"},{"time":46178,"text":"a group of young black\nand Latino drag queens"},{"time":48883,"text":"fought back against the police\nat a gay bar in Manhattan"},{"time":52529,"text":"called the Stonewall Inn,"},{"time":54549,"text":"and how this sparked\nthe modern gay rights movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58078,"text":"It was an amazing story,\nand it piqued my interest."},{"time":61417,"text":"So I decided to pick up my tape \nrecorder and find out more."},{"time":65628,"text":"With the help of a young archivist\nnamed Michael Shirker,"},{"time":69804,"text":"we tracked down all\nof the people we could find"},{"time":72381,"text":"who had been at\nthe Stonewall Inn that night."},{"time":75817,"text":"Recording these interviews,"},{"time":77814,"text":"I saw how the microphone\ngave me the license"},{"time":80043,"text":"to go places I otherwise\nnever would have gone"},{"time":82779,"text":"and talk to people I might not\notherwise ever have spoken to."},{"time":86912,"text":"I had the privilege of getting to know"},{"time":88754,"text":"some of the most amazing,\nfierce and courageous human beings"},{"time":92648,"text":"I had ever met."},{"time":94830,"text":"It was the first time\nthe story of Stonewall"},{"time":96934,"text":"had been told to a national audience."},{"time":98986,"text":"I dedicated the program to my dad,"},{"time":101249,"text":"it changed my relationship with him,\nand it changed my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108181,"text":"Over the next 15 years,\nI made many more radio documentaries,"},{"time":111617,"text":"working to shine a light on people\nwho are rarely heard from in the media."},{"time":115681,"text":"Over and over again,"},{"time":117260,"text":"I'd see how this simple act\nof being interviewed"},{"time":119860,"text":"could mean so much to people,"},{"time":122020,"text":"particularly those who had been told\nthat their stories didn't matter."},{"time":125711,"text":"I could literally see\npeople's back straighten"},{"time":128080,"text":"as they started to speak\ninto the microphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130866,"text":"In 1998, I made a documentary\nabout the last flophouse hotels"},{"time":135371,"text":"on the Bowery in Manhattan."},{"time":137762,"text":"Guys stayed up in these\ncheap hotels for decades."},{"time":140432,"text":"They lived in cubicles\nthe size of prison cells"},{"time":142824,"text":"covered with chicken wire"},{"time":144124,"text":"so you couldn't jump\nfrom one room into the next."},{"time":147088,"text":"Later, I wrote a book on the men\nwith the photographer Harvey Wang."},{"time":151067,"text":"I remember walking into a flophouse\nwith an early version of the book"},{"time":155491,"text":"and showing one of the guys his page."},{"time":158079,"text":"He stood there staring at it in silence,"},{"time":160354,"text":"then he grabbed the book out of my hand"},{"time":162653,"text":"and started running down\nthe long, narrow hallway"},{"time":166136,"text":"holding it over his head"},{"time":167645,"text":"shouting, \"I exist! I exist.\""},{"time":172010,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176863,"text":"In many ways, \"I exist\" became\nthe clarion call for StoryCorps,"},{"time":180694,"text":"this crazy idea that I had\na dozen years ago."},{"time":184270,"text":"The thought was to take\ndocumentary work"},{"time":186499,"text":"and turn it on its head."},{"time":188356,"text":"Traditionally, broadcast documentary"},{"time":190610,"text":"has been about recording interviews\nto create a work of art or entertainment"},{"time":194696,"text":"or education that is seen or heard\nby a whole lot of people,"},{"time":198944,"text":"but I wanted to try something"},{"time":200325,"text":"where the interview itself\nwas the purpose of this work,"},{"time":203473,"text":"and see if we could give many,\nmany, many people the chance"},{"time":206445,"text":"to be listened to in this way."},{"time":209069,"text":"So in Grand Central Terminal 11 years ago,"},{"time":212119,"text":"we built a booth where anyone \ncan come to honor someone else"},{"time":216492,"text":"by interviewing them about their life."},{"time":219503,"text":"You come to this booth and you're met\nby a facilitator who brings you inside."},{"time":223334,"text":"You sit across from, say, your grandfather"},{"time":225911,"text":"for close to an hour\nand you listen and you talk."},{"time":228953,"text":"Many people think of it as,\nif this was to be our last conversation,"},{"time":232645,"text":"what would I want to ask of\nand say to this person"},{"time":235640,"text":"who means so much to me?"},{"time":237916,"text":"At the end of the session,\nyou walk away with a copy of the interview"},{"time":241203,"text":"and another copy goes\nto the American Folklife Center"},{"time":243861,"text":"at the Library of Congress"},{"time":246119,"text":"so that your great-great-great-grandkids\ncan someday get to know your grandfather"},{"time":250175,"text":"through his voice and story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253548,"text":"So we open this booth\nin one of the busiest places in the world"},{"time":256705,"text":"and invite people to have this\nincredibly intimate conversation"},{"time":260188,"text":"with another human being."},{"time":261419,"text":"I had no idea if it would work,\nbut from the very beginning, it did."},{"time":266225,"text":"People treated the experience\nwith incredible respect,"},{"time":269104,"text":"and amazing conversations happened inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272471,"text":"I want to play just one animated excerpt"},{"time":275002,"text":"from an interview recorded\nat that original Grand Central Booth."},{"time":278763,"text":"This is 12-year-old Joshua Littman\ninterviewing his mother, Sarah."},{"time":283291,"text":"Josh has Asperger's syndrome."},{"time":285497,"text":"As you may know, kids with Asperger's\nare incredibly smart"},{"time":288562,"text":"but have a tough time socially."},{"time":290721,"text":"They usually have obsessions."},{"time":292370,"text":"In Josh's case, it's with animals,"},{"time":294576,"text":"so this is Josh talking with his mom Sarah"},{"time":297199,"text":"at Grand Central nine years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300499,"text":"(Video) Josh Littman:\nFrom a scale of one to 10,"},{"time":302776,"text":"do you think your life would be\ndifferent without animals?"},{"time":305758,"text":"Sarah Littman: I think it would be\nan eight without animals,"},{"time":308565,"text":"because they add so much pleasure to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310699,"text":"JL: How else do you think your life\nwould be different without them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313898,"text":"SL: I could do without things\nlike cockroaches and snakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316617,"text":"JL: Well, I'm okay with snakes\nas long as they're not venomous"},{"time":319518,"text":"or constrict you or anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320919,"text":"SL: Yeah, I'm not a big snake person --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":322778,"text":"JL: But cockroach is just\nthe insect we love to hate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325288,"text":"SL: Yeah, it really is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326821,"text":"JL: Have you ever thought\nyou couldn't cope with having a child?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329955,"text":"SL: I remember when you were a baby,\nyou had really bad colic,"},{"time":333345,"text":"so you would just cry and cry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334948,"text":"JL: What's colic?\nSL: It's when you get this stomach ache"},{"time":338105,"text":"and all you do is scream\nfor, like, four hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340590,"text":"JL: Even louder than Amy does?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342563,"text":"SL: You were pretty loud,\nbut Amy's was more high-pitched."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345907,"text":"JL: I think it feels like everyone\nseems to like Amy more,"},{"time":349111,"text":"like she's the perfect little angel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351781,"text":"SL: Well, I can understand\nwhy you think that people like Amy more,"},{"time":355644,"text":"and I'm not saying it's because\nof your Asperger's syndrome,"},{"time":358483,"text":"but being friendly comes easily to Amy,"},{"time":361487,"text":"whereas I think for you\nit's more difficult,"},{"time":363902,"text":"but the people who take the time\nto get to know you love you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367942,"text":"JL: Like Ben or Eric or Carlos?\nSL: Yeah --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370357,"text":"JL: Like I have better quality friends\nbut less quantity? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":374838,"text":"SL: I wouldn't judge\nthe quality, but I think --"},{"time":377119,"text":"JL: I mean, first it was like, Amy\nloved Claudia, then she hated Claudia,"},{"time":380887,"text":"she loved Claudia, then she hated Claudia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382914,"text":"SL: Part of that's a girl thing, honey."},{"time":384802,"text":"The important thing for you\nis that you have a few very good friends,"},{"time":388134,"text":"and really that's what you need in life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390160,"text":"JL: Did I turn out to be the son\nyou wanted when I was born?"},{"time":394409,"text":"Did I meet your expectations?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":397311,"text":"SL: You've exceeded\nmy expectations, sweetie,"},{"time":400074,"text":"because, sure, you have these fantasies\nof what your child's going to be like,"},{"time":404834,"text":"but you have made me grow\nso much as a parent, because you think --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408727,"text":"JL: Well, I was the one\nwho made you a parent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410888,"text":"SL: You were the one who made me a parent.\nThat's a good point. (Laughter)"},{"time":414375,"text":"But also because you think differently"},{"time":416199,"text":"from what they tell you\nin the parenting books,"},{"time":419102,"text":"I really had to learn to think\noutside of the box with you,"},{"time":422562,"text":"and it's made me much more creative\nas a parent and as a person,"},{"time":427368,"text":"and I'll always thank you for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429036,"text":"JL: And that helped when Amy was born?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430966,"text":"SL: And that helped when Amy was born,\nbut you are so incredibly special to me"},{"time":435800,"text":"and I'm so lucky to have you as my son."},{"time":439163,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":446980,"text":"David Isay: After this story\nran on public radio,"},{"time":449287,"text":"Josh received hundreds of letters"},{"time":451051,"text":"telling him what an amazing kid he was."},{"time":453373,"text":"His mom, Sarah, bound them\ntogether in a book,"},{"time":455602,"text":"and when Josh got picked on at school,\nthey would read the letters together."},{"time":459648,"text":"I just want to acknowledge\nthat two of my heroes"},{"time":461915,"text":"are here with us tonight."},{"time":463218,"text":"Sarah Littman and her son Josh,\nwho is now an honors student in college."},{"time":468019,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":471809,"text":"You know, a lot of people talk about\ncrying when they hear StoryCorps stories,"},{"time":475691,"text":"and it's not because they're sad."},{"time":477638,"text":"Most of them aren't."},{"time":478962,"text":"I think it's because you're hearing\nsomething authentic and pure"},{"time":482015,"text":"at this moment,\nwhen sometimes it's hard to tell"},{"time":484406,"text":"what's real and what's an advertisement."},{"time":487402,"text":"It's kind of the anti-reality TV."},{"time":489793,"text":"Nobody comes to StoryCorps to get rich."},{"time":491906,"text":"Nobody comes to get famous."},{"time":493787,"text":"It's simply an act of generosity and love."},{"time":496991,"text":"So many of these are just everyday people"},{"time":499243,"text":"talking about lives lived with kindness,\ncourage, decency and dignity,"},{"time":504375,"text":"and when you hear that kind of story,"},{"time":506372,"text":"it can sometimes feel\nlike you're walking on holy ground."},{"time":510755,"text":"So this experiment \nin Grand Central worked,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513260,"text":"and we expanded across the country."},{"time":515650,"text":"Today, more than 100,000 people\nin all 50 states"},{"time":518863,"text":"in thousands of cities\nand towns across America"},{"time":521719,"text":"have recorded StoryCorps interviews."},{"time":524064,"text":"It's now the largest single collection\nof human voices ever gathered."},{"time":528987,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":534815,"text":"We've hired and trained\nhundreds of facilitators"},{"time":537253,"text":"to help guide people\nthrough the experience."},{"time":539969,"text":"Most serve a year or two with StoryCorps"},{"time":542384,"text":"traveling the country,\ngathering the wisdom of humanity."},{"time":545821,"text":"They call it bearing witness,"},{"time":547980,"text":"and if you ask them,"},{"time":549385,"text":"all of the facilitators will tell you\nthat the most important thing"},{"time":552659,"text":"they've learned from being present\nduring these interviews"},{"time":555527,"text":"is that people are basically good."},{"time":558963,"text":"And I think for the first years\nof StoryCorps, you could argue"},{"time":561921,"text":"that there was some kind\nof a selection bias happening,"},{"time":564557,"text":"but after tens of thousands of interviews\nwith every kind of person"},{"time":567833,"text":"in every part of the country --"},{"time":569482,"text":"rich, poor, five years old to 105,"},{"time":572918,"text":"80 different languages,\nacross the political spectrum --"},{"time":577063,"text":"you have to think that maybe these guys\nare actually onto something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581277,"text":"I've also learned so much\nfrom these interviews."},{"time":584568,"text":"I've learned about the poetry\nand the wisdom and the grace"},{"time":587772,"text":"that can be found in the words\nof people all around us"},{"time":590512,"text":"when we simply take the time to listen,"},{"time":593809,"text":"like this interview"},{"time":597042,"text":"between a betting clerk in Brooklyn\nnamed Danny Perasa"},{"time":600380,"text":"who brought his wife Annie to StoryCorps\nto talk about his love for her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606632,"text":"(Audio) Danny Perasa: You see,\nthe thing of it is,"},{"time":608974,"text":"I always feel guilty when I say\n\"I love you\" to you."},{"time":611450,"text":"And I say it so often.\nI say it to remind you"},{"time":614358,"text":"that as dumpy as I am,\nit's coming from me."},{"time":617214,"text":"It's like hearing a beautiful song\nfrom a busted old radio,"},{"time":620668,"text":"and it's nice of you to keep\nthe radio around the house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623295,"text":"Annie Perasa: If I don't have a note\non the kitchen table,"},{"time":626101,"text":"I think there's something wrong."},{"time":627688,"text":"You write a love letter\nto me every morning."},{"time":629742,"text":"DP: Well, the only thing\nthat could possibly be wrong"},{"time":632271,"text":"is I couldn't find a silly pen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633804,"text":"AP: To my princess:"},{"time":634831,"text":"The weather outside today\nis extremely rainy."},{"time":637048,"text":"I'll call you at 11:20 in the morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639001,"text":"DP: It's a romantic weather report."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640817,"text":"AP: And I love you.\nI love you. I love you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643567,"text":"DP: When a guy is happily married,\nno matter what happens at work,"},{"time":646666,"text":"no matter what happens\nin the rest of the day,"},{"time":648823,"text":"there's a shelter when you get home,"},{"time":650544,"text":"there's a knowledge knowing\nthat you can hug somebody"},{"time":653097,"text":"without them throwing you downstairs\nand saying, \"Get your hands off me.\""},{"time":656644,"text":"Being married is like having\na color television set."},{"time":659271,"text":"You never want to go back\nto black and white."},{"time":661478,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664820,"text":"DI: Danny was about five feet tall"},{"time":666956,"text":"with crossed eyes\nand one single snaggletooth,"},{"time":670369,"text":"but Danny Perasa had\nmore romance in his little pinky"},{"time":674061,"text":"than all of Hollywood's\nleading men put together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677174,"text":"What else have I learned?"},{"time":679077,"text":"I've learned about the almost\nunimaginable capacity"},{"time":681979,"text":"for the human spirit to forgive."},{"time":684162,"text":"I've learned about resilience\nand I've learned about strength."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687807,"text":"Like an interview with Oshea Israel\nand Mary Johnson."},{"time":691150,"text":"When Oshea was a teenager,\nhe murdered Mary's only son,"},{"time":695701,"text":"Laramiun Byrd, in a gang fight."},{"time":698186,"text":"A dozen years later, Mary went to prison"},{"time":700786,"text":"to meet Oshea and find out\nwho this person was"},{"time":703526,"text":"who had taken her son's life."},{"time":706475,"text":"Slowly and remarkably,\nthey became friends,"},{"time":709261,"text":"and when he was finally released\nfrom the penitentiary,"},{"time":711955,"text":"Oshea actually moved in next door to Mary."},{"time":715321,"text":"This is just a short excerpt\nof a conversation they had"},{"time":718526,"text":"soon after Oshea was freed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722079,"text":"(Video) Mary Johnson: My natural son\nis no longer here."},{"time":725051,"text":"I didn't see him graduate,\nand now you're going to college."},{"time":728835,"text":"I'll have the opportunity\nto see you graduate."},{"time":732132,"text":"I didn't see him get married."},{"time":734593,"text":"Hopefully one day, I'll be able\nto experience that with you."},{"time":738502,"text":"Oshea Israel: Just to hear you\nsay those things and to be"},{"time":741199,"text":"in my life in the manner\nin which you are is my motivation."},{"time":744859,"text":"It motivates me to make sure\nthat I stay on the right path."},{"time":749616,"text":"You still believe in me,"},{"time":751543,"text":"and the fact that you can do it\ndespite how much pain I caused you,"},{"time":755119,"text":"it's amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757209,"text":"MJ: I know it's not an easy thing\nto be able to share our story together,"},{"time":763106,"text":"even with us sitting here\nlooking at each other right now."},{"time":765869,"text":"I know it's not an easy thing,\nso I admire that you can do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771616,"text":"OI: I love you, lady.\nMJ: I love you too, son."},{"time":780156,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":786372,"text":"DI: And I've been reminded countless times\nof the courage and goodness of people,"},{"time":791526,"text":"and how the arc of history\ntruly does bend towards justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796588,"text":"Like the story of Alexis Martinez,\nwho was born Arthur Martinez"},{"time":801069,"text":"in the Harold Ickes projects in Chicago."},{"time":803693,"text":"In the interview, she talks\nwith her daughter Lesley"},{"time":806526,"text":"about joining a gang as a young man,"},{"time":808894,"text":"and later in life transitioning\ninto the woman she was always meant to be."},{"time":813724,"text":"This is Alexis and her daughter Lesley."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816223,"text":"(Audio) Alexis Martinez: One of the most\ndifficult things for me was"},{"time":819482,"text":"I was always afraid that\nI wouldn't be allowed"},{"time":822408,"text":"to be in my granddaughters' lives,"},{"time":825287,"text":"and you blew that completely\nout of the water,"},{"time":827585,"text":"you and your husband."},{"time":828909,"text":"One of the fruits of that is,\nin my relationship with my granddaughters,"},{"time":832369,"text":"they fight with each other sometimes\nover whether I'm he or she."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835946,"text":"Lesley Martinez: But they're free\nto talk about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838433,"text":"AM: They're free to talk about it,\nbut that, to me, is a miracle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841489,"text":"LM: You don't have to apologize.\nYou don't have to tiptoe."},{"time":844791,"text":"We're not going to cut you off,\nand that's something I've always"},{"time":849372,"text":"wanted you to just know,\nthat you're loved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852337,"text":"AM: You know, I live this every day now."},{"time":854682,"text":"I walk down the streets as a woman,\nand I really am at peace with who I am."},{"time":859806,"text":"I mean, I wish I had a softer voice maybe,"},{"time":862460,"text":"but now I walk in love\nand I try to live that way every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871562,"text":"DI: Now I walk in love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874906,"text":"I'm going to tell you\na secret about StoryCorps."},{"time":877808,"text":"It takes some courage\nto have these conversations."},{"time":881193,"text":"StoryCorps speaks to our mortality."},{"time":883584,"text":"Participants know this recording\nwill be heard long after they're gone."},{"time":887601,"text":"There's a hospice doctor named Ira Byock"},{"time":890285,"text":"who has worked closely with us\non recording interviews"},{"time":892829,"text":"with people who are dying."},{"time":894286,"text":"He wrote a book called\n\"The Four Things That Matter Most\""},{"time":897051,"text":"about the four things you want to say\nto the most important people in your life"},{"time":900882,"text":"before they or you die:"},{"time":903924,"text":"thank you, I love you,"},{"time":906455,"text":"forgive me, I forgive you."},{"time":909682,"text":"They're just about the most powerful words\nwe can say to one another,"},{"time":913212,"text":"and often that's what happens\nin a StoryCorps booth."},{"time":916718,"text":"It's a chance to have a sense of closure\nwith someone you care about --"},{"time":920095,"text":"no regrets, nothing left unsaid."},{"time":922917,"text":"And it's hard and it takes courage,"},{"time":926354,"text":"but that's why we're alive, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":931299,"text":"So, the TED Prize."},{"time":933802,"text":"When I first heard from TED\nand Chris a few months ago"},{"time":936779,"text":"about the possibility of the Prize,\nI was completely floored."},{"time":940615,"text":"They asked me to come up\nwith a very brief wish for humanity,"},{"time":944186,"text":"no more than 50 words."},{"time":945950,"text":"So I thought about it,\nI wrote my 50 words,"},{"time":948694,"text":"and a few weeks later,\nChris called and said, \"Go for it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":953381,"text":"So here is my wish:"},{"time":956329,"text":"that you will help us"},{"time":959278,"text":"take everything we've learned\nthrough StoryCorps"},{"time":962018,"text":"and bring it to the world"},{"time":964781,"text":"so that anyone anywhere\ncan easily record a meaningful interview"},{"time":968798,"text":"with another human being\nwhich will then be archived for history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973715,"text":"How are we going to do that? With this."},{"time":978393,"text":"We're fast moving into a future\nwhere everyone in the world"},{"time":982071,"text":"will have access to one of these,"},{"time":984114,"text":"and it has powers I never\ncould have imagined 11 years ago"},{"time":987945,"text":"when I started StoryCorps."},{"time":989895,"text":"It has a microphone,"},{"time":991358,"text":"it can tell you how to do things,"},{"time":993669,"text":"and it can send audio files."},{"time":996200,"text":"Those are the key ingredients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998522,"text":"So the first part of the wish\nis already underway."},{"time":1001726,"text":"Over the past couple of months,"},{"time":1003305,"text":"the team at StoryCorps\nhas been working furiously"},{"time":1006300,"text":"to create an app that will bring\nStoryCorps out of our booths"},{"time":1009760,"text":"so that it can be experienced\nby anyone, anywhere, anytime."},{"time":1015193,"text":"Remember, StoryCorps has always\nbeen two people and a facilitator"},{"time":1018874,"text":"helping them record their conversation,\nwhich is preserved forever,"},{"time":1022839,"text":"but at this very moment,"},{"time":1024887,"text":"we're releasing a public beta version\nof the StoryCorps app."},{"time":1028533,"text":"The app is a digital facilitator\nthat walks you through"},{"time":1031720,"text":"the StoryCorps interview process,"},{"time":1034105,"text":"helps you pick questions,"},{"time":1035777,"text":"and gives you all the tips you need"},{"time":1037867,"text":"to record a meaningful\nStoryCorps interview,"},{"time":1040676,"text":"and then with one tap upload it \nto our archive at the Library of Congress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046197,"text":"That's the easy part, the technology."},{"time":1049337,"text":"The real challenge is up to you:"},{"time":1051715,"text":"to take this tool and figure out\nhow we can use it"},{"time":1054913,"text":"all across America and around the world,"},{"time":1057878,"text":"so that instead of recording\nthousands of StoryCorps interviews a year,"},{"time":1061462,"text":"we could potentially record\ntens of thousands"},{"time":1064232,"text":"or hundreds of thousands"},{"time":1066188,"text":"or maybe even more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069355,"text":"Imagine, for example,\na national homework assignment"},{"time":1073093,"text":"where every high school student\nstudying U.S. history across the country"},{"time":1077087,"text":"records an interview\nwith an elder over Thanksgiving,"},{"time":1079989,"text":"so that in one single weekend"},{"time":1082892,"text":"an entire generation of American lives\nand experiences are captured."},{"time":1087977,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1095812,"text":"Or imagine mothers on opposite\nsides of a conflict somewhere in the world"},{"time":1099354,"text":"sitting down not to talk\nabout that conflict"},{"time":1102976,"text":"but to find out who they are as people,"},{"time":1105173,"text":"and in doing so,\nbegin to build bonds of trust;"},{"time":1109128,"text":"or that someday it becomes\na tradition all over the world"},{"time":1112014,"text":"that people are honored\nwith a StoryCorps interview"},{"time":1114522,"text":"on their 75th birthday;"},{"time":1116765,"text":"or that people in your community"},{"time":1119041,"text":"go into retirement homes or hospitals\nor homeless shelters or even prisons"},{"time":1124195,"text":"armed with this app to honor the people\nleast heard in our society"},{"time":1127725,"text":"and ask them who they are,\nwhat they've learned in life,"},{"time":1130711,"text":"and how they want to be remembered."},{"time":1133172,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1140947,"text":"Ten years ago, I recorded\na StoryCorps interview with my dad"},{"time":1144224,"text":"who was a psychiatrist,\nand became a well-known gay activist."},{"time":1149019,"text":"This is the picture\nof us at that interview."},{"time":1152456,"text":"I never thought about that recording\nuntil a couple of years ago,"},{"time":1155637,"text":"when my dad, who seemed\nto be in perfect health"},{"time":1158632,"text":"and was still seeing patients\n40 hours a week,"},{"time":1161233,"text":"was diagnosed with cancer."},{"time":1163996,"text":"He passed away very suddenly\na few days later."},{"time":1167386,"text":"It was June 28, 2012,"},{"time":1169661,"text":"the anniversary of the Stonewall riots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1174041,"text":"I listened to that interview\nfor the first time at three in the morning"},{"time":1177398,"text":"on the day that he died."},{"time":1179126,"text":"I have a couple of young kids at home,"},{"time":1181123,"text":"and I knew that the only way\nthey were going to get to know this person"},{"time":1184582,"text":"who was such a towering figure in my life\nwould be through that session."},{"time":1189428,"text":"I thought I couldn't believe in StoryCorps\nany more deeply than I did,"},{"time":1193173,"text":"but it was at that moment"},{"time":1194961,"text":"that I fully and viscerally grasped\nthe importance of making these recordings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1199820,"text":"Every day, people come up to me"},{"time":1201913,"text":"and say, \"I wish I had interviewed\nmy father or my grandmother or my brother,"},{"time":1206074,"text":"but I waited too long.\""},{"time":1208342,"text":"Now, no one has to wait anymore."},{"time":1210478,"text":"At this moment,"},{"time":1212158,"text":"when so much of how we communicate\nis fleeting and inconsequential,"},{"time":1215700,"text":"join us in creating this digital archive"},{"time":1218197,"text":"of conversations that are\nenduring and important."},{"time":1222514,"text":"Help us create this gift to our children,"},{"time":1225344,"text":"this testament to who\nwe are as human beings."},{"time":1229342,"text":"I hope you'll help us make\nthis wish come true."},{"time":1233268,"text":"Interview a family member, a friend\nor even a stranger."},{"time":1237779,"text":"Together, we can create an archive\nof the wisdom of humanity,"},{"time":1244069,"text":"and maybe in doing so,"},{"time":1245703,"text":"we'll learn to listen a little more\nand shout a little less."},{"time":1249665,"text":"Maybe these conversations will remind us\nwhat's really important."},{"time":1254193,"text":"And maybe, just maybe,"},{"time":1256956,"text":"it will help us recognize\nthat simple truth"},{"time":1259742,"text":"that every life, every single life,"},{"time":1263689,"text":"matters equally and infinitely."},{"time":1266624,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1268755,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1270905,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."},{"time":1275113,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1277389,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1279571,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}